## Project conventions

Before answering or editing code, load the relevant convention files:

- @.ai/instructions/coding-conventions.md
- @.ai/instructions/architecture.md
- @.ai/instructions/testing.md
- @.ai/instructions/security.md

These contain the project's coding style, layering rules, test expectations,
and security posture. Treat them as authoritative — if something here conflicts
with them, they win.

## Source layout

```
src/application/      Use cases, services, orchestration
src/domain/           Pure business logic (entities, value objects, interfaces)
src/infrastructure/   DB, network, drivers, external adapters
src/presentation/     Entry points (HTTP routers, CLI, ISRs)
tests/{unit,integration,e2e,performance}
```

Empty directories may be prefixed with `_` (e.g. `_e2e/`) — that prefix is
removed when the directory gets its first real file.

